Just because the whineplay has gone, doesn't mean you are all allowed to stop posting comments back to Verant. The very fact it is no longer there may well improve the signal to noise ration enough that we can get through to them.<br>
<br>
I just made the following post there myself, with the intent of being both non-confrontational and non-specific to wizards. They don't respond well to rudeness (understandably) and in honesty, I think they probably ignore wizard rants too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  So just try to make lucid arguments and lets erode away whatever opposition they have.<br>
<br>
8&lt;-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
My concern is fairly simple, but echoed throughout the EQ community and something we would all truly love to hear an official standpoint on.<br>
<br>
Simply put, at a given level offensive spells no longer balance with the corresponding melee damage. Spell damage has remained static whilst no one would contest melee items have improved hugely.<br>
<br>
Not only this, but as the game has evolved, monsters have become progressively more hit point laden and magic resistent.<br>
<br>
This manifests itself in two ways. Firstly, one is no longer able to contribute consistently fair amounts of damage in a standard grouping situation. Melees will contribute more damage than offensive casters by a considerable margin. Secondly, the ability to help crowd control by burning a monster to the ground in a few casts no longer exists in the new world. In lower guk, were there too many pulls a druid or wizard could remove a monster from the equation fairly quickly and pay a price in down time. This holds true for neither Kunark and even more so Velious. Sadly this reinforces the enchanter requirement in most new world dungeons.<br>
<br>
I'm certain you are aware of this, but I'm desperately hoping you are considering ways to address what is a very important issue to a lot of players. The extremely rare eye and robe from Cazic himself don't really address the problem.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
Cassius Runeblaze,<br>
